I. In: Alt. CHI (2007)<span class=\"Occurrences\"><span class=\"Occurrence OccurrenceGS\"><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" class=\"google-scholar-link gtm-reference\" data-reference-type=\"Google Scholar\" href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?q=Harrison%2C%20S.%2C%20Tatar%2C%20D.%2C%20Sengers%2C%20P.%3A%20The%20three%20paradigms%20of%20HCI.%20In%3A%20Alt.%20CHI%20%282007%29\"><span><span>Google Scholar</span></span></a></span></span></div></li><li class=\"Citation\"><div class=\"CitationNumber\">10.</div><div class=\"CitationContent\" id=\"CR10\">Bannon, L.: From human factors to human actors: the role of psychology and human-computer interaction studies in system design. In: Greenbaum, J., Kyng, M. (eds.) Design at Work, pp. 25\u201344. L. Erlbaum Associates Inc., Hillsdale (1992)<span class=\"Occurrences\"><span class=\"Occurrence OccurrenceGS\"><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" class=\"google-scholar-link gtm-reference\" data-reference-type=\"Google Scholar\" href=\"http://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=From%20human%20factors%20to%20human%20actors%3A%20the%20role%20of%20psychology%20and%20human-computer%20interaction%20studies%20in%20system%20design&amp;author=L.%20Bannon&amp;pages=25-44&amp;publication_year=1992\"><span><span>Google Scholar</span></span></a></span></span></div></li><li class=\"Citation\"><div class=\"CitationNumber\">11.</div><div class=\"CitationContent\" id=\"CR11\">Grudin, J., Pruitt, J.: Personas, participatory design and product development: an infrastructure for engagement. In: Proceedings of the Participatory Design Conference, Malmo, Sweden (2002)<span class=\"Occurrences\"><span class=\"Occurrence OccurrenceGS\"><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" class=\"google-scholar-link gtm-reference\" data-reference-type=\"Google Scholar\" href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?q=Grudin%2C%20J.%2C%20Pruitt%2C%20J.%3A%20Personas%2C%20participatory%20design%20and%20product%20development%3A%20an%20infrastructure%20for%20en